The paper deals with the analysis of Support Vector Machines (SVM) with $\ell_1$ penalty, which is a common tool in machine learning and data analysis. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses concepts from probability theory and Banach spaces, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Additionally, the paper deals with sparsity constraints, which is a common theme in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
